HSC Survey Results

Scots Bay Survey # 11 Results from 09/10/2023

Survey Details

4 commercial purse seiners conducted this fishing survey on 09/10/2023 starting at 19:00:00, which was 2.12 hours before hide tide.

All vessels ran two transects each in the Main Survey Box.

There was a plankton tow and replicate conducted and CTD cast by Lady Janice II.

No tags were applied during this survey.

Since no fish were caught, no samples were obtained for target strength estimation.

Tides Tables

Tide Schedule for Margaretsville NS, Station #315m Source: www.waterlevels.gc.ca

Acoustic Equipment

Each vessel was equipped with a Simrad ES38-18/200-18C combi (2-in-1) transducer prior to the survey that contains a 38kHz split beam and 200 kHz single beam transducer. Data was logged to the computer hard-drive for post-processing. All participating boats were calibrated on 38kHz before the survey.

Survey Results

Main Results

The results are subject to change as DFO will re-evaluate data editing, area estimation and apply a target strength.

Preliminary biomass prediction for Scots Bay using standardized parallel transects is 3,388mt, and with turnover applied 2,971mt.

Vessel Performance

Speed

Average vessel speed was 8.81. This is above the 8 knot requirement; vessels are urged to slow down to prevent backscatter noise from interfering with the acoustic data.

Distance

No significant distance was cut from the planned lines; vessels covered the planned area well.
